{"copyright": {"licenseType": "NO", "determinationType": "OTHER", "thirdPartyContentCondition": "NOT_SET"}, "subjectCategories": ["PLASMA PHYSICS"], "exportControl": {"isExportControl": "NO", "ear": "NO", "itar": "NO"}, "created": "2013-08-14T09:38:00.0000000+00:00", "distributionDate": "2019-07-11T00:00:00.0000000+00:00", "center": {"code": "CDMS", "name": "Legacy CDMS", "id": "092d6e0881874968859b972d39a888dc"}, "onlyAbstract": false, "sensitiveInformation": 2, "fundingNumbers": [{"number": "NSF ATM-88-11128", "type": "CONTRACT_GRANT"}, {"number": "NAGW-846", "type": "CONTRACT_GRANT"}, {"number": "DE-FG05-80ET-53088", "type": "CONTRACT_GRANT"}, {"number": "F49620-86-K-0004", "type": "CONTRACT_GRANT"}], "abstract": "Two-dimensional electrostatic and electromagnetic particle-in-cell codes are used to investigate plasma beam propagation across transverse magnetic fields. Both large- and small-ion-gyroradius beams are studied in the case of small beam momentum or energy (low drift kinetic beta). Large-ion-gyroradius beams with a large dielectric constant epsilon much greater than (M/m) to the 1/2 (where M/m is the ion-to-electron mass ratio) are found to propagate across the magnetic field via E x B drifts at nearly the initial injection velocity. Beam degradation and undulations are observed, in agreement with previous experimental and analytical results. When epsilon is of order (M/m) to the 1/2 the plasma beam propagates across field lines at only half its initial velocity and loses its coherent structure. When epsilon is much less than (M/m) to the 1/2 the beam particles decouple at the magnetic field boundary, scattering the electrons and deflecting the ions slightly.", "title": "Numerical investigation of a plasma beam entering transverse magnetic fields", "stiType": "REPRINT", "distribution": "PUBLIC", "submittedDate": "2013-08-14T09:38:00.0000000+00:00", "isLessonsLearned": false, "authorAffiliations": [{"sequence": 0, "submissionId": 19900025873, "meta": {"au